<HEAD>Fish Kills Man</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fisherman died after a gar fish
jumped out of the water and cut his neck, a newspaper reported
today.
   The fish, a forktail alligator gar, struck fisherman Anthony
Fernando, 21, Monday night, the Sun newspaper reported. He died
before fellow fishermen could get him to a hospital, the paper said.
   The paper quoted his brother, Nisantha, as saying the incident
occurred off the southwestern coast of the island. He speculated
that the fish, one of a number jumping in the water at the time,
had been attracted by a light on their boat.
