<HEAD>Bus Crash In Central China Kills 39</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus plunged 260 feet into a ravine in central
China, killing 39 people and injuring the other 17 on board, the
official Xinhua News Agency reported.
   The Chinese-built bus was making a turn at the bottom of a hill
in Henan province on Monday when it swung off the road and fell,
the agency said. The crash immediately killed 33 people and six
others died later in the hospital, said the report, monitored in
Tokyo.
   All the survivors were injured, but the report did not say how
seriously.
   Police were investigating how the accident occurred, Xinhua said.
   Several bus and train accidents have been reported in China in
recent weeks, with more than 100 people reported killed.
