<1ST_LINE>r a PM-RedLightJumper     03-08 0237</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Red Light Jumper,0244</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Parachutes Off Downtown Chicago Building, Lands On Car At
Light</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man parachuted off a downtown building, landing
on a car that was stopped at a red light, then jumped into another
car and fled, police said today.
   Officer Thomas Karczewski said police had no suspects but were
checking a license plate number provided by Musiliu Alagbala, whose
car was hit by the parachutist Monday afternoon.
   Karczewski said today he didn't think the parachutist was
injured.
   Witnesses told police the parachutist jumped off a building that
was under construction and landed on the hood of Alagbala's car.
   Alagbala, 38, ``was waiting at the light when he saw a man roll
off the hood with a parachute on,'' Patrolman Charles Weyer said
Monday.
   ``He folded up his parachute, went running across the street and
jumped into a car,'' said Bonnie Panagakis, 39, of Palatine, who
saw the incident.
   Mrs. Panagakis said she saw a man flying ``higher than the light
poles'' above the Chicago River.
   ``I think he saw he was about to go into the river, and he had
to get himself righted,'' she said.
   She said that he maneuvered his parachute back toward the street
but that the parachute was torn by a lamppost. ``That's when he
landed on the guy's hood,'' she said.
   Alagbala said the man caused between $300 and $500 damage to the
car.
</TEXT>
