<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Haitians Intercepted,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Coast Guard Stops Almost 500 Haitians in Three Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Coast Guard vessels have stopped almost 500
Haitians attempting to enter the United States illegally in the
past three days, a spokesman said today.
   Since Saturday three cutters have intercepted four sailing
vessels crammed with Haitians off the Bahamas, said service
spokesman Luis Diaz.
   The figures in the past three days have almost doubled the
number of Haitians stopped this year, he said, adding the weather
alone could not explain the sudden surge in interdictions.
   ``The seas are calm at the moment, but it definitely has to be
the economic situation in their country,'' said Diaz.
   On Saturday a sailing vessel with 192 people was stopped off
Great Inagua, and since then three other ships have been stopped
near Crooked Island, said Diaz.
   One intercepted today had 90 aboard ``and still counting,'' said
Diaz.
   The 1,186 total since Jan. 1 is running well ahead of last
year's total of 3,556 people caught and returned to Haiti, he said.
</TEXT>
