<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sudan-Meningitis,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Meningitis Epidemic in Khartoum; 20 Dead, 600 Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Health Ministry declared a meningitis
epidemic Tuesday, saying 20 people have died of the disease in
recent days and 600 are hospitalized.
   Meningitis normally strikes in Sudan every summer, but this year
it began a month earlier than usual early because of unseasonably
early high temperatures. The temperature Tuesday was 111 degrees
Fahrenheit.
   The Health Ministry said Khartoum has been declared an
``epidemic-hit area'' and added the government was using all its
capabilities to deal with the situation.
   It said another 148 cases have been reported from other regions
in Sudan.
   The statement said the disease was widely spread within
overcrowded shanty towns around the capital, where an estimated
750,000 people from southern Sudan are seeking refuge from famine
and civil war in the south.
</TEXT>
