<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Jewel Theft,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thieves Steal $1.6 Million in Jewels From Store</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves tunneled into a jewelry store through the
floor of an adjacent hotel, silenced its alarms and stole $1.6
million in gems, according to a news report.
   Burglars using a blowtorch cut open a safe in the Furst jewelry
store and took out keys that opened a second safe where the jewels
were kept, the Italian news agency ANSA reported Monday.
   The thieves entered the store by cutting a hole in the floor of
the Hotel Majestic that was closed for renovation and silenced the
alarms by cutting telephone lines and pulling one alarm out of the
wall, ANSA said.
   Store owner Manlio Bertucci, 36, said someone tried to break
into the downtown store several years ago by throwing hand grenades
through the front window. He said metal blinds kept the thieves
from getting into the store.
</TEXT>
