<1ST_LINE>r a AM-CityStalker     03-08 0253</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-City Stalker,0259</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Center City Stalker Tabbed In Seven Cases</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DON BEMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven women have been attacked in the last
month by the ``Center City Stalker,'' who forces them into secluded
areas of downtown buildings, robs them, ties them up and sometimes
rapes them, police said.
   The Stalker strikes day or night, with the latest attack at 8
a.m. Monday in the lobby of a downtown building, say police, who
speculate he may be a security guard because he showed a badge to
one victim.
   Police Commissioner Kevin Tucker has formed a special 24-hour
task force.
   ``My dad will pick me up from work every day this week until
they catch that animal,'' said Diane Mills, a Federal Express
employee said.
   Police have distributed composite drawings to office buildings
and businesses, and Federal Express couriers dropped off copies of
a police sketch as they made deliveries Tuesday.
   Monday night, police swarmed the streets after the latest victim
gave a description that matched ones from victims in four of the
other six cases.
   The 20-year-old woman was on her way to a class near City Hall
when she was grabbed near an elevator, police said. The man dragged
her at gunpoint into a secluded spot, robbed her of two gold chains
and a diamond-studded gold watch.
   One man has been arrested and charged with robbery and attempted
rape in another case. But none of the seven Stalker victims could
identify him in a lineup, police said.
</TEXT>
