<DOCNO> AP880308-0153 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-88 0537EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--BusGunshot     03-08 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bus Gunshot,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunshot Puts Hole In School Bus Seat, Bruises Child</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUMMERVILLE, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old boy on Monday accidentally
fired a .38-caliber handgun into a seat on a school bus carrying
about 45 children, bruising a child's knee, authorities said.
   The 9-year-old boy was suspended pending investigation, and the
7-year-old boy who was bruised did not require medical attention,
authorities said.
   ``We believe that the child didn't know what he was doing _ it
was just a prank,'' said Sandra Lindsay, assistant superintendent
for instruction.
   The bus was about a mile from Knightsville Elementary School,
which both children attended, when the gun discharged as the boy
was trying to unload it, Mrs. Lindsay said. She said he got the gun
from his parents' home.
   The bullet went through the bus seat, ricocheted and bounced off
the knee of a boy two seats behind. Mrs. Lindsay said the bullet
didn't pierce the boy's pants, but caused a small bruise.
   The children on the bus were being counseled by school nurses,
guidance counselors and principals, and none appeared extremely
upset, said Bob Flowers, transportation director.
</TEXT>
