<1ST_LINE>d a PM-Obit-Chambers     03-08 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Chambers,0147</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New Castle Courier-Times veteran dies at 80</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW CASTLE, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Scott B. Chambers, editor of the New
Castle Courier-Times for 50 years, has died. He was 80.
   Chambers, who died Monday in the Henry County Memorial Hospital,
was part owner of the Courier-Times until the Chambers family sold
it to Nixon Newspapers Inc. in 1986.
   ``Scott was a major force for both freedom of the press and in
the development and welfare of New Castle,'' said Wes Rowe,
publisher of the Courier-Times.
   Chambers was graduated from Indiana University in 1930 and
became managing editor of the paper when the Chambers family
purchased the Courier and consolidated it with the Times, which the
family already owned.
   When Chambers' father, Walter S. Chambers Sr., became ill in the
late 1940s, Scott Chambers became both editor and publisher of the
Courier-Times.
</TEXT>
