<HEAD>Indian Air Force Plane Crash Kills 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An air force transport plane crashed
shortly after takeoff Tuesday, killing 12 people, five of them on
the ground, a news agency reported.
   The plane, which was not further identified, crashed over a
four-square-mile area near Cuttack, in eastern Orissa state, the
United News of India reported.
   In addition to the five villagers killed by debris from the
crash, eight others were injured and more than 40 homes and stores
were damaged, the news agency said.
   The plane was bound for New Delhi. The air force is
investigating the cause of the crash.
