<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Waldheim     03-08 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Waldheim,0195</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Waldheim Accepts Invitation to Visit Kuwait</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUWAIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Austrian Foreign Ministry official said Tuesday
that President Kurt Waldheim has accepted an invitation to visit
Kuwait and that Austria would not bow to ``Zionist threats,'' a
news agency reported.
   The official Kuwait News Agency quoted ministry general
secretary Thomas Klestil as telling it that Waldheim received the
invitation from the emir, Sheik Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah, ``with all
appreciation and welcome'' and would visit ``at the earliest
convenient time.''
   It would be Waldheim's second visit to an Arab country following
the world furor raised over his service in the German army during
World War II.
   KUNA quoted Klestil as saying that Austria ``will not succumb to
Zionist threats and pressures to remove President Kurt Waldheim
from his office.''
   Klestil is on a tour of Persian Gulf Arab nations following a
visit by Iran's foreign minister, Ali Akbar Velayati, to Vienna,
Austria's capital.
   Kuwait and neighboring noncombatant states are pressing for
international efforts to convince Iran to end its war with Iraq,
now in its eighth year.
   Waldheim has visited Jordan, the Vatican and Pakistan since his
election.
</TEXT>
