<2ND_LINE>PM-Federated,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Macy's Starts Bid for Federated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A subsidiary of R.H. Macy & Co. Inc. launched
a cash tender offer today to buy 80 percent of Federated Department
Stores Inc., which remains the target of a competing buyout offer
from Campeau Corp.
   A wholly-owned Macy subsidiary, FDS Acquisition Corp., commenced
the cash tender offer at a price of $74.50 per share for up to
70.43 million shares, or approximately 80 percent, of Federated
common stock. Macy plans to swap shares in the merged company
Macy's-Federated Inc. for the remaining 20 percent of Federated
stock.
   Analysts have estimated the total value of the Macy offer at
$6.1 billion.
   The tender offer is proceeding under a definitive agreement
signed by Federated and Macy last week.
   Toronto-based Campeau is offering $75 per share for 80 percent
of Federated's stock and $44 per share for the remaining stock. The
Campeau offer, which has a blended value of $68 per share, totals
$6.18 billion.
   Campeau's offer expires at midnight March 15, while the Macy
offer expires April 4.
   Federated stock was unchanged at $66.62{ at midday today on the
New York Stock Exchange.
