<2ND_LINE>BC-US-Scotland-Bank,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bankers Trust To Set Up Operation In Scotland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bankers Trust New York Corp., the nation's
eighth-largest bank holding company, said Monday it will establish
a major operation in Edinburgh, Scotland, to provide global custody
facilities for British and European owners and managers of large
investment funds.
   Scottish Office Industry Minister and Member of Parliament Ian
Lang, said through the Scottish Development Agency here that the
move is an important boost for the expanding financial services
industry in Scotland.
   Bankers Trust already has 400 employees in Scotland through its
acquisition last August of Edinburgh-based World Markets Company,
which provides global financial information services. The new
operation will add another 150 jobs.
   A spokesman for the Scottish Development Agency's North American
offices, said that more than $158 billion in funds is managed in
Scotland, making it the second-largest financial services sector
behind London in the European Economic Community.
</TEXT>
