<FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-88 1630EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f PM-WallStreetClosing 1stAdd   03-08 0084</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Closing, 1st Add,0090</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NEW YORK: busy pace.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 24.70 points to
2,081.07, the highest level since the October stock market crash.
   Gainers outpaced losers by 2-to-1 on the New York Stock
Exchange, with 1,067 up, 532 down and 396 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 237.68 million vs. 152.98 million the
previous session.
   The NYSE's composite index rose 1.09 to 151.62.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index rose 1.90
to 296.04.
