<1ST_LINE>d f BC-ComexChairman     03-08 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Comex Chairman,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Elect New Comex Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John H. Hanemann was elected Tuesday to a
two-year term as chairman of Commodity Exchange Inc., the world's
most active metals market.
   Hanemann, a senior partner of Prestige Metal Trading Co., was
elected to a two-year term at the annual meeting of COMEX members,
the futures exchange reported.
   It was the first direct election of the chairman by the full
membership in the exchange's 55-year history.
   Hanemann succeeds Alan J. Brody, who will remain COMEX president
and chief executive.
   Re-elected to the board were John D. Coffin, Martin Presler,
Salvatore DeMicoli and Robert Hussa. Elected to the board for the
first time were Jack Gandolfo, Robert B. Harmon Jr., Steven
Karvellas, Mel Schnell, Leo Walsh and Salvatore Azzara.
   Futures traded on the COMEX include gold, silver, copper and
aluminum.
</TEXT>
